Police arrested two men in separate incidents for the illegal possession of firearms and ammunition last week. Manenberg police spokesperson, Captain Ian Bennett, says: “During stop-and-search operations in Tambo Village, one man was arrested in Amanda Street as he was walking down the street. “The second suspect was arrested in Manenberg Avenue in possession of a 7.65 pistol with one live round. “Manenberg police will not allow criminals to take our community hostage by firing random shots as if Manenberg is a firing range.” V 
  Anyone with information regarding any illegal gang activity can call Manenberg Police Station on 021 699 9400 or Crime Stop on 0860 010 111. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  